The '''Makira starling''' ('''''Aplonis dichroa'''''), also known as the '''San Cristobal starling''', is a [[species]] of [[starling]] in the family [[Sturnidae]]. It is [[endemic]] to the [[Solomon Islands]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is [[subtropical]] or [[tropical]] moist lowland [[forest]]s.

